name: Oliver Simser
snippet: My experience at this macdonalds was OK. The service was fast, but the burger was not very well made, the sauce was uneven and there was too much lettuce. The lettuce was everywhere is the box. On the plus side they had a great lobby. Overall not the best

name: Arghavan Rastegari
snippet: Absolutely fresh, delicious, and good temperature poutines! The service was so fast and efficient. The staff were really nice and helpful. I asked for less gravy on one of them and that’s why it’s less in the picture. Fair prices and really convenient and close location to grab something to eat in work breaks! Overall, it was a pleasant experience. Price range 💵: $$ - Follow me for more reviews ☺️ My Instagram: @mortgagebyarghavan

name: Azure4 JohnDu
snippet: Good location and Great service.... Order a meal, missing a drink, however, the manager provide a good alternative witj good manager.... Feel care free having meal here.. Thanks McDonald, give us great stuffs serve here... Will keep come for Lunch and other meals....

snippet: Messed up every single item in my order. Missing fries, nugget sauce and straws. Would not answe phone when I called to complain. The coke was not sealed properly and 80% of it spilled and spiked the food. Lazy and careless staff.

name: Afrin K
snippet: Gets really busy in morning rush hour (around 9am) but otherwise usually they’re fast and consistent with their service. Upstairs seating section is also very nice

name: Nahum Lopez Lopez

snippet: i work at the bay across the street and came to grab my food on my break. i came back to my work only to see that my large fries are basically half empty. my break isn’t long so i can’t even go back to complain. why are u guys being cheap on the fries?? it literally looks like someone ate half my fries.

snippet: This McDonald's is alright, they're quick and have a separate station for McCafe entirely so morning coffee orders and handled swiftly. name: Slavik Liman

name: RKS

name: RUPERT YOUNG

name: Jaideep Singh

name: Joseph Greene

name: Anita Windisman

snippet: First time at this Mcdonald on king street location coming from another province, we entered this place to but food and my young daughter wanted to take some photos to share her experience with friends but an employee standing behind cash counter suddenly started yelling at us" this is a private property, you can not take any photos/video, you need to delete any photo/video immediately" the employee then walked from behind the cash counter to front entrance where both my daughter and I were standing, this employee caused an embarrassing situation for us in the store and demanded my daughter delete any photo/video she may have taken, the fact is if I was not hungry at approx 11pm-12am after a long day of wedding rehearsal, etc. Plus staying in hotel, i would have exchange few words with the employee who does not know how to treat customers, I've lived in Ontario prior to moving to another province, am not aware of Mcdonald fast food restaurants not allowing people to take photos inside the restaurant, hence there is no signage warning customers of such restrictions/ rules, although this may be the case but employee could have kindly approach my young child and explain to her the photo taking restrictions/rules. Dear Mcdonald restaurants across Canada please make public service announcement to inform Canadian consumers about your strict no photo/video policies inside your restaurants this way another customer(minor) does not suffer such an embarrassment inside your store in the presence of other customers.

name: Eazaz Khan

name: Kevin Fouillet
snippet: They don’t know how to do a BigMac... seriously. The employee was drunk making burgers...

name: Jennifer S
snippet: The location has the best staff, they are usually always happy and upbeat. They can get pretty busy but they move the line really fast. They have never messed up my order and I go there all the time. I like the quality of the food and the service. I've been to the surrounding McDonald's and this one is my favourite. The restaurant is clean and the dinning area is also very clean.

name: c橙
snippet: This location is always very clean when I pass through. Their breakfast sandwiches are my favourite as they're usually fresh and hot, but the more standard burgers are pretty hit or miss. Sometimes it's very obvious how long the patties have been sitting in a heated drawer. I've never personally found the soft serve machine to be down at this location!

name: Ibraheem Aziz
snippet: Large location with ample seating and a classic McDonald's menu. Staff here are efficient and do a great job of taking and preparing orders in a timely manner. Tends to get fairly busy during rush hour, and conveniently located close to parking and public transit.

name: Ritwik Bose
snippet: Manager was really rude to me, annoying. I wish they also put more salt on the fries, there salt level is so little on the fries you can barely even feel it. Saying this because the fries have been very lightly salted on many occasions

name: Sarah Chandler
snippet: I visited twice, the first time I had a long wait for a bacon chicken ranch wrap. The wrap was good, but I waited for a long time. The next time I ordered a few items and one sandwich was missing. Just a couple of misses, I'm sure these were anomalies but something to keep in mind. The food is good, people are friendly.

name: Dave Curran
snippet: Been here many times over the years because I work close by and can't recall one single time that my food was actually fresh. Today I was served a burger that had obviously been sitting in the warmer for hours and had to throw it out after one mealy, soggy bite. I would fire any employee who thinks its acceptable to serve food like that that to a paying customer because they clearly don't care.

name: Rita Pot
snippet: Visited last night. We were a large group. Came to have some coffees and chat. The young kids loved the fish tank. Very fast service for our large order. Coffee great. Service was great. Would return when in the area as the atmosphere was very nice to catch up with loved ones.

name: Sam Ataei
snippet: Worst McDonald's ever. I ordered a coffee at 1040 pm, but they already closed the restaurant when it was supposed to be open until 11 pm. After 15 mins they gave the coffee, which was cold ( colder than at room temperature)

name: Y V E S
snippet: They're not wearing gloves before and also during this pandemic. I've seen them frequently touch their face and other surfaces before making burgers. It's kinda gross in my opinion.

name: Robert Arnone
snippet: Very affordable (obviously!). It was late at night, closer to midnight; so they were on their smaller staff. The line up was pretty long, took about 7 minutes to get our order placed. After placed the order came pretty quick after that. Since it was late at night, McDonald's are the only places open. So for being the evening shift, very good level of service. Washrooms were a little messy, and the evening clientele didn't scream safest environment.

name: Apurv Ray
snippet: Decent space inside this mcdonalds enough to keep your distance in this pandemic. Easy to form queues while maintaining your distance.

name: Bria Trudeau
snippet: Wi-Fi was down so the lovely team members hooked my coffee up for free because they knew I was in a rush!! Bless!!

name: Jas Sharma
snippet: The staff was not helpful and friendly. They were unable to understand a small request despite being repeated 7 times and they were very cold towards what we wanted to order. We had to eventually change our order. On our way back, we heard someone say outside that this one is probably the worst McDonald's.

name: Keith
snippet: This place is busy no matter what time of day so the only thing you could hope for is competent staff. In most cases, this has always been true...until this morning (June 10, 9:30am). After already waiting 10+ minutes to try their new bagel and a coffee, the "supervisor" decides that she is going to start calling out drinks while people wait for their food. Why? Nobody knows. Why didn't she use the number system that they have in place? Nobody knows. She just started calling out random drinks and because nobody knew what she was doing, nobody took them (because like good sheep, we wait for our number to be called and take our whole meal at once). So she gets annoyed, visibly. And when my food is finally ready and I ask for my coffee, she tirades the poor guy twice who was running orders because he couldn't figure out the mess she created. She needs a nice quiet location in the suburbs where she can boss people around, not one of the busiest stores in the city (and he needs a medal for having to put up with her). Asides from that, the bagel was not worth the wait.

name: Shahram Shams
snippet: I liked it. It's clean and neat. Has friendly staff and the service was fast. I recommend this place to everyone.

name: Wolfgang Gomille
snippet: Got what I wanted quickly and without errors. Don't know why McDonald's doesn't offer the Chicken Mcmuffin all day long. Probably because they define it as a breakfast sandwich. Yet the 2 for $5 breakfast sandwiches all day long promotion excludes the Chicken Mcmuffin. Make up your mind McDonald's, either offer it all day long, or include it in the breakfast sandwich category and promos.

name: Zinedin Farhan
snippet: The man in the front who helps the courier is such a nice guy. Loved his work.This is an appreciation review.

name: Paul Waldie
snippet: I grabbed a coffee and a sausage, egg Mcmuffin here and the staff were quick and very polite. Not a lot of room to eat at the location but if you do then your refill is free. A definite recommend.

name: Jyoti Parkash
snippet: I visited place last week. It was quite good until I asked them for mayo as a complimentary product. But they said we would charge you for this. I love McDonald's so I am not going say any bad thing about food or the brand. But never bring yourself to this place unless you are so hungry and no other restaurant is open

name: Jeremy Tsui
snippet: I don't rate many places with five stars but they get this cause it's consistent from one McDonald's to the other. You know how terrible the meat patties taste universally. There is a second level for more seating at this location with a cleaner helping you take away your trays. A first for this kind of service.

name: Alb Vas
snippet: Crazy busy place, but they're always well staffed and I've been here over 10 times, and they've always smiled and done well for me. I'm very happy with this place. I've never visited the upstairs seating area or the bathrooms so I can't attest to this. But in general, lots of staff make sure you get your food, and keep the place clean.

name: akshay cherian
snippet: The customer service is poor because most of the time when I order the triple triple coffee they either forget to put the sugar or stir it. Maybe this is because of untrained people at the front section. Too bad I lose my money for the bad coffee they make for me and there is no other option for me because I work near to this place and there is no other alternative.

name: Edward Fine
snippet: just came back from McDonald's it was quite good it was a very hot day so I pulled in for some ice cream and the ice cream machine does work and it was cold and it was quick. Overall it was a great experience and the air conditioning works perfectly and it's nice clean seats so I'd highly recommend McDonald's for a nice hot day to visit and cool down a bit

name: Rahul Sharma
snippet: The only reason why my review says 1 start is cos its the least possible. I have been here about 10-15 times now (just because its next building to my workplace) and have never walked out of there before 7-8 minutes even when I order a single coffee. I am not even going during rush hours. If you ask the staff about the delay they look at you like they will punch you in the face. I even tried informing them about a fly in the muffins pantry (did not click a picture so no proof) but all I got was "Yaa, we will remove it". I do not understand how this place is not shutdown yet.

name: David Malek
snippet: Some of the staff are very intense. They might give you dirty looks for asking questions or not hearing them where they have to repeat themselves. The music is kind of intense and tacky too. Mostly hip hop and teenage type of pop music, probably too much for a franchise coffee shop. You almost feel like you are eating inside a night club. On the plus side, the two storey layout is pretty good.

name: Danosaurus
snippet: Nice place with two floors. Really quick service and not a lot of people there. Currently the seating his of course closed due to covid, but it is one of the nicest mcdonald's I have seen.

name: Crystabel Neilson
snippet: The Angus burger patty was warm and the fries were fairly fresh. I've been to this location many times. The service is decent and the restaurant is pretty clean. Overall, a good McDonald's experience.

name: Megan Nadia
snippet: Great service. Really busy it seems so food is always freshly fried. The people there work really hard and provide amazing service at all hours. Usually the place to go for late night eats after the clubs

name: Amarita Singh Diez
snippet: My order gets screwed up almost everytime. Syrup is missing for pancakes multiple times. Yogurt and apple slices are expired or the milk expires the next day. No other McDonald's offer these items with expiration dates or so close to it. Waited over 20 minutes twice for my meal and a drink when there were only 2-4 people in the restaurant.

name: Johanna Belle
snippet: I ordered the Big Mac and McChicken combo. Upon arrival the bread was hard and doughy, the meat looked grey and was cold. I understand McDonalds is not a 5 star dining experience but I would hope that they would at least make the conscious effort to make it an edible meal.

name: Ayan T
snippet: A decent McDonald's location. Was passing through the area with my wife and friend. Its a very busy location but its nice that it s newly renovated. The new machines to make orders were having issues with the tapping with cards and the upstairs was a bit dirty/sticky. I don't think the staff ever wipes down the seats or booth seats because they have oil and dirt all over them.

name: Mike Banz
snippet: realy McDonalds?!!worst employee, only online order after 10pm.do not come from canada and the app cannot be found, answer employee: your problem, bye!!

name: Ashok Sahu

name: Shaun Morgan
snippet: They were pretty fast and accurate but the new staff they hired, does not know how to multitask. There's always atleast one homeless person that asks for change. I usually will buy them something as I would rather not just give away my hard earned money.

name: oluwaseun oladutele
snippet: Can’t believe they still prepare food with wearing gloves.. how safe is it to touch people’s food with your hand 🤚.. Not safe

name: K. Johnson
snippet: Pretty fast service. Restroom is near the main entrance. There are stairs which lead to a lounge like area and this place has a lot of seating for large groups and even if eating alone. Generally clean and not too crowded.

name: Stevan Jovanovski
snippet: Extremely slow staff in the evening. Two people were ahead of me. It took the staff of 4 people 5 minutes to get one guys 2 cheeseburgers made, another 6 for a Big Mac and then another 6 to make my wrap... The way he wrapped it, I got a mouth fill of lettuce in the beginning, a huge bite of bacon and finished with a couple bites full of mayo. You could tell the manager running this gong show has no idea what he’s doing while he’s looking through all the different trays, not knowing what is what and in a panic. If you don’t work well under pressure, don’t work at McDonald’s.

name: Square Pixels Canada
snippet: Almost great place for a quick bit but not good if you want dinner or a party. Staff is all Indian student who doesn't understand fluent English and takes so much time preparing and taking orders. Also they can't stop looking at the couples sitting, which makes the situation weird. But the kiosk system helps quite good and makes the on the go process very fast. However, the staff sometimes make mistakes preparing the order but not all the time. The location is not 100% visible from all directions but it can be found pretty easily, make sure to check properly that you are entering through the McDonald's door not the Subway's because they are attached side by side. I have visited there around 20-25 times and the only thing that I do not appreciate is the staff's English. If all tye Canadian staff is working here, the ordering process can be faster by 30-50%.

name: Noak L
snippet: Manager named Daniel failed to treat customer with respect. This outfit caused me inconvenience today, stole my time and provided zero value or service. A simple “sorry” would have been nice.

name: Kim
snippet: Every time I go to this location, it always takes painstakingly long to get my order. This time however I got a bit more frustrated, first being that they forgot to give me my extra condiments that I ordered. Luckily I checked my bag before leaving but I had to walk back up to the counter and show them my receipt in order to get my condiments that I paid for. Little did I know that when I returned home with my food order that I would find a very disappointing surprise. The Mc chicken sandwich in my combo that I ordered seemed a little flat and when I opened it up to add my condiments I saw that there was no chicken patty in my Mc chicken sandwich! Such a big mistake that can’t be excusable. I’m usually not one to complain or write reviews of this nature but I was really HANGRY at this point. I immediately called the location manager and spoke to them but all they can do was give me a name and advise me to go in, in the next two days to get a complementary sandwich- which is out of my way since I had bought it enroute Downtown on my way home. Since I’m already writing this review, while I was there their drink counter had a dirty dish rag that was left there from the last worker that was trying to attempt cleaning it but didn’t finish the job. I know it’s not a five-star restaurant but this is definitely my last time going to this McDonald’s location for my cheat meal. Since I had to give them my receipt to prove that I purchased my condiments at the counter I wasn’t able to get the receipt number to file a complaint on their official Website with a reference number so I hope they see this review and take it as an opportunity to coach their employees and work on that franchise location.

name: Paul Friday
snippet: Had to wait forever for a simple breakfast sandwich and muffin. People way behind me in the lineup were being served first. The staff didn't seem to know what they were doing. Staff preparing food in the back weren't wearing gloves. One of them had a massive plummer bum going on. Ruined my breakfast. I've noticed it's been harder and harder to get "fast" food at McDonald's now that those stupid order screens popped up.

name: R A
snippet: The food was good, and the seating area ( 2 stories) was very nice. the main draw were the "computers" you could use to place your order. They worked well and made the process much simpler.

name: Derek Dresser
snippet: Ok for a downtown location seperate coffee bar which is now never open. This year dollar drink days is a disaster

name: RIddler
snippet: I usually visit around 4PM and it's usually quiet around this time. Definitely try their specials. Service is good and orders usually roll out fast.

name: Carl Johnson
snippet: I work at a different McDonald's from Hamilton and was here visiting for the WWE show and stopped by for a quick bite. This store was slow literally took 10 minutes for a mcwrap meal. But seeing the amount of workers they had back there (8-9) and only 1 person running for window it was a no brainer it would take awhile.. And only 1 manager doing almost everything from being on till, running for window, working kitchen and managing. *sigh* why isn't there 2 managers working at the same time? The shocking part during the wait was a dude running in and trying to steal from the donation box. When he didn't smash the box hard enough he ran through the counter and tried stealing a cup before an employee caught him and escorted him out. Only time I've seen something like that happen and it was shocking.. overall though very small but spacious restaurant for the upstairs part! just slow service..

name: Sheryl Gamboa
snippet: The store very clean no problem for that. The only disgusting is the one who in-charge doing orders they don't use gloves yak yak yak yak they holding bread, burger by hands.... Please check for this? To the management for sure you have camera you will no who is not using gloves...Thanks so much...

name: Trevor Levine
snippet: I recent started getting coffee at the McCafé counter around 8 am but it wasn't open at 655 today so despite no wait to order at the regular cash it really should not have taken 5-6 minutes to prepare and serve one coffee, as it did. Make a coffee, serve a coffee: instead the process seems to be make 4 coffees, carry 4 coffees 10 feet and have someone else call the order number and hand it out. Process is important but completely unnecessary in that case.

name: T Choulli
snippet: I wish if there was a 0 star. Worst customer service ever not from the employee but the manager. His name is Daniel with a Latino accent. Very arrogant, makes faces as I’m talking. He repeated the order over and over again to give us a wrong order at the end. For the record, the order was 4 combos and a sandwich, what’s there to get wrong. The disrespect, rudeness and lack of customer service made this the worst breakfast experience.

name: Scott Buttenham
snippet: Location is notoriously slow in terms of service. Often see employees hanging out in the back doing nothing. Frustrating to typically need to ask for my food so they’ll start making it after waiting 10 min, especially when it’s 11PM on a Tuesday and the restaurant is practically empty...

name: bobak mahtash
snippet: Extremely slow service. I made a quick order of chicken nuggets, but had to leave after 10 min b/c I was about to miss my GO bus, and couldn't get my order on time. This has happened to me twice on this location. Not very happy with the customer service either!

name: Dean Mallette
snippet: Usually good, but today I went there to get some burgers. There was a supervisor demonstrating how to make a burger to another employee. Neither were wearing gloves and both handled the bun, cheese and beef patties with their bare hands.

name: Annemieke Smit-Roeland
snippet: It took them 10 minutes to prepare a McFlurry and then they handed it out to the wrong person too.. We corrected them on time, by showing our corresponding order number. Staff didn't seem to work well together.

name: Himani Bhasin

This is not an atypical reception for us, so I stated 1) he was a service dog 2) legally allowed to enter and 3) motioned to his vest. When I motioned my boyfriend over, the guard deferred to the manager, who instantly ok'd us. After the manager left, the guard continued to interrogate us and insisted I show identification, which is not a thing in Canada. He eventually walked away when when we kept repeating that same answer. Legally you can only ask 1) if he/she is a service dog 2) what tasks they perform. My service dog was perfectly calm and wellbehaved throughout those 15 minutes, and was necessary in preventing a panic attack/blackout. Very hesitant to return here.
